Package com._360t.simple.singleprocess

Class SingleProcessCallFromJarApp

  • java.lang.Object
    • com._360t.simple.singleprocess.SingleProcessCallFromJarApp
  • public class SingleProcessCallFromJarApp
extends java.lang.Object

    Single Process App which should be called only through existing jar file of application

    This class is used to define an endpoint of execution through main method. The main method is able to analyze input string args value and extract sending parameters and send its parameter to the runner class. The runner class will be created base on the input parameters and run into its java process.

                                                  java.lang.String jarFileName)
                                           throws java.io.IOException
        getPlayerProcess method which receive couple of parameters and create a java process and run the specified runner class
        Parameters:
        clazz - The class type of the specified runner class.
        threadNumber - The number of thread which a executor is created.
        messageNumber - The number of messages will be exchange between both players.
        delayMilliSeconds - The delly milliseconds which will be exist between every message transmission.
        initiatorMessage - The initiator message value
        jarFileName - The jar file name which this program will execute through that.
        Returns:
        a java.lang.Process instance which responsible to executing passed runner class.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - The exception is throws when an error is occurred.
